<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN297">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>perunīr mēva ṟaṇṇaṭai yerumai</l>
<l>yirumarup puṟaḻu neṭumā ṇeṟṟiṉ</l>
<l>paimpaya ṟutirtta kōtiṉ kōlaṇaik</l>
<l>kaṉṟuṭai maraiyā tuñcuñ cīṟūr</l>
<l>kōḷivaṇ vēṇṭēm puravē nārari</l>
<l>naṉaimutir cāṭi naṟaviṉ vāḻttit</l>
<l>tuṟainaṉi keḻīik kampu ḷīṉun</l>
<l>taṇṇaṭai peṟutalu murittē vainnuti</l>
<l>neṭuvēl pāynta mārpiṉ</l>
<l>maṭalvaṉ pōntaiyiṉ niṟku mōrkkē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>The little village where wild cows sleep that possess calves</l>
<l>near the stalks of waste shed from the fresh crop</l>
<l>of long glorious kernels that resemble the dark horns</l>
<l>of the buffalo in the (rice-producing) village attached to the great water,</l>
<l>we do not want here to take [it] as a boon. Praising it </l>
<l>like the toddy in the jar matured with [spicy] buds, filtered through fibres,</l>
<l>obtaining the (rice-producing) village too is rightful </l>
<l>where water fowl much gathers by the ghat/harbour [and] multiplies,</l>
<l>for those who stand like palmyra trees, strong with fronds,</l>
<l>[their] chests leapt upon by sharp-tipped long spears. </l>
</lg>
    </div>
